!                               *****IFWINTY*****
! 
!     This module defines Fortran parameter constants and
!     derived data types  for use with both the 32-bit (_M_IX86)
!     and 64-bit versions of the NT4 and WIN2000 operating systems.  
!
! 
!     The base version is: 
!
!           Microsoft Platform Software Development Kit (SDK)
!                for Windows Server 2003 R2
!
!     As with the C header files distributed with the SDK, there
!     is only one common set of files for both 64-bit and 32-bit
!     operating systems.
!   
!     Within the Fortran versions of the header files, the
!     following symbols are used to control the compilation.
!
!     _M_IA64 conditionally compiles items for Intel(R) IA-64 architecture systems
!     _M_IX86 conditionally compiles items for Intel(R) IA-32 architecture systems
!     _M_X64 or __x86_64__ conditionally compiles items for the Intel(R) 64 systems
!
!Items in ifwinty which might be more usefully treated as
!Fortran character strings have been conditionally
!defined that way.  Look for the following and define the
!symbol if you wish to keep the old C-like definitions of these
!items as arrays of characters.
!
!IF DEFINED(__KEEP_OLD_CHARACTER_ARRAYS)
!
!
!In some cases, we really do want the character array.
!So the conditional will on the following symbol:
!DEC$ DEFINE __SELECT_CHARACTER_ARRAYS  
!**********************************************************
!*Note: the above line actually defines the symbol, and we*
!*      always want it to be defined.                     *
!**********************************************************
!
!
!     Known problems: 
!
!   
!     03-16-01 There are a number of derived types which should be
!              packed rather than naturally aligned.  This is
!              controlled by ALIGNMENT_IS_PACKED_IA64.  If this
!              symbol is defined if _M_IA64 is defined, several
!              of the samples which use T_OPENFILENAME fail.
!              Until it is determined why the more recent PSKDs
!              show some structures as packed when they only work
!              when naturely aligned, this symbol will not be defined.
!
!              Note: T_BITMAPFILEHEADER does need to be packed.
!
!
!    04-25-01  Access to the latest PSDK in INCLUDE\PRERELEASE has given
!              us the opportunity to determine which data types should be
!              packed, and which data types should not be packed. The
!              directives will be edited, and then turned on.
!
